penalty_scale)`

Objective used by \code{nlminb()} for the optimizer-based projected interval.
\code{par} holds \verb{(muDelta, logORdelta)}, \code{candidate_fun} builds the joint
candidate, \code{threshold} is the chi-squared cutoff, \code{direction} chooses whether
the optimizer is minimizing or maximizing \code{Delta}, and \code{penalty_scale}
controls the quadratic penalty for violating the joint constraint. The helper
returns a scalar numeric objective value. Its role is to convert the
constrained projection problem into an unconstrained box optimization.
}

